# Asset Pipeline Standards

This document defines standards for game asset formats, compression, streaming, and management.

---

## Asset Formats

### Texture Formats

| Use Case | Format | Compression | Notes |
|----------|--------|-------------|-------|
| Albedo/diffuse | BC1/DXT1 | Yes | 4bpp, no alpha |
| Albedo + alpha | BC2/DXT3, BC3/DXT5 | Yes | 8bpp |
| Normal maps | BC5/3Dc | Yes | Two-channel |
| HDR | BC6H | Yes | Float |
| UI | RGBA8, ASTC | Platform-dependent | Uncompressed for crisp text |

### Mesh Formats

| Format | Use Case | Vertex Attributes |
|--------|----------|-------------------|
| GLTF/GLB | Runtime, interchange | Position, normal, UV, tangent |
| FBX | Authoring, animation | Full pipeline |
| Custom binary | Optimized load | Stripped, quantized |

### Audio Formats

| Use Case | Format | Compression | Sample Rate |
|----------|--------|-------------|-------------|
| Music | Vorbis, Opus | Lossy | 44.1kHz |
| SFX (short) | WAV, ADPCM | Lossless/low | 22-44kHz |
| Voice | Opus | Lossy | 24kHz |
| Ambient | Vorbis | Lossy | 44.1kHz |

---

## Compression

### Texture Compression

- [ ] Use platform-appropriate formats (BC on PC/console, ASTC/ETC2 on mobile)
- [ ] Mipmaps generated at build time
- [ ] Normal maps use appropriate format (BC5 for XY, derive Z)
- [ ] Avoid over-compression for UI (artifacts visible)

### Mesh Compression

- [ ] Quantize vertex positions (16-bit or float)
- [ ] Index buffer optimization (vertex cache friendly order)
- [ ] LOD meshes generated in pipeline, not at runtime
- [ ] Skinned meshes: bone indices and weights quantized

### Audio Compression

- [ ] Short SFX (< 1s): uncompressed or ADPCM for low latency
- [ ] Long audio: Vorbis/Opus for size
- [ ] Streaming audio: use streaming decode, not load-all

---

## Streaming

### Streaming Strategy

| Asset Type | Strategy | Trigger |
|------------|----------|---------|
| Level geometry | Stream by zone | Player proximity |
| Textures | Stream by mip/region | Visibility, distance |
| Audio | Stream from disk | Playback start |
| Scripts/code | Load at level init | Level load |

### Streaming Checklist

- [ ] Streaming zones defined with overlap to prevent pop-in
- [ ] Priority system: visible > nearby > distant
- [ ] Memory budget per asset type enforced
- [ ] Unload assets when zone is far enough
- [ ] Async loading never blocks main thread during gameplay

---

## Level of Detail (LOD)

### Mesh LOD

| LOD | Distance | Reduction | Switch Hysteresis |
|-----|----------|-----------|-------------------|
| 0 | 0-20m | 100% | |
| 1 | 20-50m | 50% | 5m |
| 2 | 50-100m | 25% | 10m |
| 3 | 100m+ | 10% | 20m |

- [ ] LOD transitions use hysteresis to avoid flickering
- [ ] Billboards or impostors for very far objects
- [ ] LOD generated in pipeline, not at runtime

### Texture LOD (Mipmaps)

- [ ] All textures have mipmaps
- [ ] Anisotropic filtering for angled surfaces
- [ ] Virtual texture / streaming atlas for large worlds

---

## Texture Atlasing

### Atlas Rules

- [ ] Static UI elements in atlases (reduce draw calls)
- [ ] Sprites for 2D games in atlases
- [ ] Padding between sprites to avoid bleeding (2-4px)
- [ ] Power-of-two atlas dimensions when required by API
- [ ] Atlas layout documented for artists

### Atlas Build

```
Sources: sprite_1.png, sprite_2.png, ...
Output: ui_atlas.png + ui_atlas.json (uv coordinates)
```

---

## Audio Management

### Audio Categories

| Category | Max Simultaneous | Priority | Behavior |
|----------|------------------|----------|----------|
| Music | 1 | Low | Crossfade |
| Voice | 2-4 | High | Duck music |
| SFX | 16-32 | Medium | Pool, limit |
| Ambient | 4-8 | Low | Spatial blend |

### Audio Pipeline

- [ ] Audio sources use pooling (no per-sound allocation)
- [ ] Distance-based attenuation and culling
- [ ] Occlusion/obstruction for spatial audio
- [ ] Master volume and per-category mixing

---

## Asset Bundles

### Bundle Strategy

| Bundle | Contents | Load Trigger |
|--------|----------|--------------|
| Boot | Splash, loading UI | Game start |
| Common | Shared fonts, UI | First menu |
| Per-level | Level geometry, textures | Level load |
| DLC | Optional content | User selection |

### Bundle Checklist

- [ ] Dependencies between bundles documented
- [ ] No circular bundle dependencies
- [ ] Bundle size within platform limits
- [ ] Incremental builds for fast iteration
- [ ] Version hashing for cache invalidation

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Asset formats chosen per platform
- [ ] Compression applied appropriately
- [ ] Streaming implemented for large worlds
- [ ] LOD system for meshes and textures
- [ ] Atlases for UI and sprites
- [ ] Audio categories and pooling defined
- [ ] Asset bundles structured for load order
